Introduction

Kim Tae-Woo is a South Korean singer, musical actor and TV personality, he's best known for being the lead vocalist of the boy group g.o.d.
He debuted as a member of g.o.d on January 13, 1999 under SidusHQ, and debuted as a solo artist in 2006 after g.o.d announced their indefinite hiatus.

In 2022, he signed with IOK Company.
